TB60.\n\nThis extension allows the user to export and import folders and messages with lots of options, for example:\n\n<b>Tools Menu --&gt; ImportExportTools or Context menu on folders panel --&gt; Import/Export</b>\n- export of folder in a single file (mbox format), with also the subfolders if you want;\n- export of all messages in single files (eml or html or plain text format or CSV), with attachments and an index;\n- export of all messages in PDF format (required ImportExportTools 3.0 or higher)\n- export of all messages in one single plain text file;\n- export of index of the messages in a folder (HTML or CSV format);\n- mbox files import;\n- eml files import;\n- emlx files import;\n- import of all the eml files existing in a directory;\n- export of all files of all mail files of --&gt; Save selected messages</b>\n- saving multiple messages in eml/html/plain text format with just one click;\n- saving multiple messages in PDF format with just one click (required ImportExportTools 3.0 or higher)\n\n<b>Message menu --&gt; Copy to clipboard or Context menu of thread panel --&gt; Copy to clipboard</b>\n- copy the message or all headers to clipboard.\n\n<b>Context This extension allows you to choose a specific sort order for your folders, allowing you to put the most important ones on top, and manually order them.\n\nThis extension also offers another method for automatically sorting folders. Unlike Thunderbird's default, the extension's sort method takes into account Unicode special characters. If you do not wish to sort everything manually, you can use Unicode symbols at the beginning of your folder names to put them on top. Check out the <a href=\"https://github.com/TB-throwback/LookOut-fix-version/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Git Repository</a> to contribute.</strong>\n\n<strong>Thunderbird Beta Users Please Note:</strong> Initial support is under development and available through the <a href=\"https://github.com/TB-throwback/LookOut-fix-version/releases\" rel=\"nofollow\">Git Repository</a> for testing\n\nOriginal LookOut add-on by Aron Rubin for Mozilla Thunderbird is abandoned September 30, 2011:\n<a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/addon/lookout/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://addons.mozilla.org/addon/lookout/</a>\n\nDoes it mean its death? I brought it back to life!\nNow it is called LookOut (fix version) and works with all new Thunderbird versions.\n\nLookOut (fix version) - based on last version LookOut+ 1.2.15 by Attila K. Mergl (Last Updated: October 15, 2013)\n<a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/addon/lookout-1/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://addons.mozilla.org/addon/lookout-1/</a>\n\n<strong>Please before use, remove or disable the original LookOut and LookOut+ !</strong>\n\n=====================\nWhat is LookOut?\n\nLookOut is a plugin which allows Thunderbird (and SeaMonkey) to interface with Microsoft's mail tools by decoding metadata and attachments encapsulated/embedded in a TNEF encoded attachment (aka <strong>winmail.dat</strong>). \nThe TNEF decoding engine was inspired (with permission) by the <a href=\"http://tnef.sf.net/\" rel=\"nofollow\">TNEF project</a>. It can synchronize on the My Contacts group, all contacts, or all contacts and groups (with mailing lists).  Many mobile devices and some other sync apps only synchronize with the My Contacts group, so most people can choose that option after logging in for the first time.\n\n*Important*\nNOTE: Mailing lists are buggy, but gContactSync tries to work around these bugs whenever possible.  The fake e-mail addresses nobody...@nowhere.invalid are necessary to prevent bugs in mailing lists.  It is best to drag contacts into the main address book and add them to groups from Google's interface.\n\nDon't try to delete or rename \"My Contacts\", \"Coworkers\", \"Family\", or \"Friends\" or you may have to 'reset' that address book.\n\nTutorial/Demo (work in progress): <a href=\"http://www.pirules.org/extensions/gcontactsync/tutorial/intro.php\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.pirules.org/extensions/gcontactsync/tutorial/intro.php</a>\n\nIt makes several modifications and improvements to the Address Book including more fields and types for several fields.\n\nSupported applications:\n<ul><li>Thunderbird 2 and up (including 3.0 and 3.1)</li><li>Seamonkey 2 and up</li><li>Icedove (Debian-branded Thunderbird)</li><li>Support for Postbox coming soon</li></ul>\nPlease read the Developer Comments as well."},"developer_comments":{"en-US":"You may synchronize one account with several address books, synchronizing an address book with only one group of your choice, and can import contacts from Facebook and Twitter.&lt;br&gt;\n\nIf you choose to synchronize all contacts and groups don't try to delete or rename \"My Contacts\", \"Coworkers\", \"Family\", or \"Friends\" or you may have to 'reset' that address book. module ajoute un symbole dans le panneau d'en-tête du message pour basculer entre une vue compacte et détaillée. La vue compacte peut être configuré sur une ou deux lignes.\n\nUne boîte de dialogue de personnalisation est accessible par un clic-droit dans le panneau d'en-tête des messages.\n\nAttention, ce module est incompatible avec CustomizeHeaderToolbar <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/thunderbird/addon/45601\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://addons.mozilla.org/thunderbird/addon/45601</a>\n\nLe raccourci clavier \"MAJ + h\" permet de basculer entre la vue compacte et détaillée.\n\nCe module intègre également la fonctionnalité de «RSS Linkify Sujet\" par Alex Dedul (<a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/1704)\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/1704)</a>.\n\nIl y a aussi une option pour n'afficher que les adresses e-mail dans la vue compacte.\n\nSi vous souhaitez utiliser la dernière version, vous la trouverez sur le canal du développement du module, en bas de cette page.\n\nSi vous rencontrez un bug merci de le rapporter sur le fil dédié de Mozillazine (en Anglais): <a href=\"http://forums.mozillazine.org/viewtopic.php?f=29&amp;t=1405155\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://forums.mozillazine.org/viewtopic.php?f=29&amp;t=1405155</a>","en-US":"For Thunderbird 68.0 or newer you can use the beta version available at <a href=\"https://github.com/jmozmoz/compactheader/releases\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/jmozmoz/compactheader/releases</a>\n\nFor versions older then Thunderbird 37 use version 2.0.9 (see the <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/de/thunderbird/addon/compactheader/versions/\" rel=\"nofollow\">version histroy</a>)\n\nThunderbird does not anymore have the ability to reduce the display size of header pane to one line (as in Thunderbird 2.0). This add-on adds a symbol to compact and expand the message header plane. The compact header view mode can be set to either one or two lines.\n\nA customization dialog can be opened for the toolbar in the header pane (right mouse button context menu) to change the displayed buttons and their style.\n\nThe shortcut \"SHIFT+h\" can be used to toggle between expanded and compact header view.\n\nThis add-on integrates the functionality of \"RSS Linkify Subject\" by Alex Dedul (<a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/1704)\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/1704)</a>.\n\nThere is also an option to display only the email addresses in the compact header view. Another option enables darkening the message header, if the message pane has focus.\n\nIf you want to use the latest version, look for it at <a href=\"http://compactheader.mozdev.org/installation.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://compactheader.mozdev.org/installation.html</a> There you will find the latest beta versions.\n\nThere are several bug reports about a disappearing header pane in the compact header view mode. Please make sure to use version <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/thunderbird/addon/mail-merge/versions/5.6.0\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>5.6.0</strong></a>.\n\n<strong>Version 6.0.0 for Thunderbird 68:</strong>\nMail Merge is fully compatible with Thunderbird 68. Please make sure to use version <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/thunderbird/addon/mail-merge/versions/6.0.0\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>6.0.0</strong></a>.\n\nOtherwise: <a href=\"https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/thunderbird-add-ons-frequently-asked-questions#w_how-do-i-update-an-add-on\" rel=\"nofollow\">Check for Updates in the Add-ons Manager</a>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Description:</strong>\nIf you want to send a message to multiple recipients, there are a few common problems:\n\n1) When you add the recipients in the To field, the recipients will see each other. (You can work around this problem by adding the recipients in the Bcc field.)\n\n2) Most email providers limit the number of recipients in the To / Cc / Bcc field. (You can work around this problem by creating multiple messages.)\n\n3) You cannot personalize the message. (You cannot work around this problem.)\n\nYou can work around some of these problems, but especially the last problem cannot be solved without creating individual messages. Of course there are third party services, that help you to send newsletters; but you have to trust them.\n\nMail Merge solves these problems by creating individual messages for each recipient from a draft message - locally on your computer without the need to trust third party services!\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Step by Step:</strong> (Address Book)\nScreenshots: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205597.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205598.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205599.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205618.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mail Merge Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205624.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Message Dialog</a>\n<ol><li>Create a New Message (\"File -&gt; New -&gt; Message\")</li><li>Add the Recipients to To or add the Variable(s) to To, e.g.: <em>{{PrimaryEmail}}</em> or <em>{{FirstName}} {{LastName}} &lt;{{PrimaryEmail}}&gt;</em></li><li>Add other Recipients to Cc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add other Recipients to Bcc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Subject (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Body (variables are supported)</li><li>Add (global) Attachments (optional)</li><li>Click \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\"</li><li>Select \"Address Book\" and check \"Deliver Mode\"</li><li>Add (individual) Attachments (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Check \"Start\", \"Stop\" and \"Pause\" (optional)</li><li>Click \"OK\"</li></ol>The Draft Message is saved as Template in your Current Account and for each Recipient a New Message is automagically saved in your Outbox (\"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\"). Ready for Delivery: \"File -&gt; Send Unsent Messages\"\n\n\n<strong>Step by Step:</strong> (CardBook)\nScreenshots: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205597.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205602.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205603.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205617.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mail Merge Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205624.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Message Dialog</a>\n<ol><li>Create a New Message (\"File -&gt; New -&gt; Message\")</li><li>Add the Recipients to To or add the Variable(s) to To, e.g.: <em>{{email}}</em> or <em>{{firstname}} {{lastname}} &lt;{{email}}&gt;</em></li><li>Add other Recipients to Cc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add other Recipients to Bcc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Subject (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Body (variables are supported)</li><li>Add (global) Attachments (optional)</li><li>Click \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\"</li><li>Select \"CardBook\" and check \"Deliver Mode\"</li><li>Add (individual) Attachments (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Check \"Start\", \"Stop\" and \"Pause\" (optional)</li><li>Click \"OK\"</li></ol>The Draft Message is saved as Template in your Current Account and for each Recipient a New Message is automagically saved in your Outbox (\"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\"). Ready for Delivery: \"File -&gt; Send Unsent Messages\"\n\n\n<strong>Step by Step:</strong> (CSV)\nScreenshots: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205600.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205601.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205619.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mail Merge Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205623.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview File Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205624.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Message Dialog</a>\n<ol><li>Create a New Message (\"File -&gt; New -&gt; Message\")</li><li>Add the Variable(s) to To, e.g.: <em>{{Email}}</em> or <em>{{FirstName}} {{LastName}} &lt;{{Email}}&gt;</em></li><li>Add other Recipients to Cc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add other Recipients to Bcc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Subject (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Body (variables are supported)</li><li>Add (global) Attachments (optional)</li><li>Click \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\"</li><li>Select \"CSV\" as \"Source\" and check \"Deliver Mode\"</li><li>Add (individual) Attachments (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Select the \"File\" and check \"Character Set\", \"Field Delimiter\" and \"Text Delimiter\"</li><li>Check \"Start\", \"Stop\" and \"Pause\" (optional)</li><li>Click \"OK\"</li></ol>The Draft Message is saved as Template in your Current Account and for each Recipient a New Message is automagically saved in your Outbox (\"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\"). Ready for Delivery: \"File -&gt; Send Unsent Messages\"\n\n\n<strong>Step by Step:</strong> (JSON)\nScreenshots: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205600.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205601.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205620.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mail Merge Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205623.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview File Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205624.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Message Dialog</a>\n<ol><li>Create a New Message (\"File -&gt; New -&gt; Message\")</li><li>Add the Variable(s) to To, e.g.: <em>{{Email}}</em> or <em>{{FirstName}} {{LastName}} &lt;{{Email}}&gt;</em></li><li>Add other Recipients to Cc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add other Recipients to Bcc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Subject (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Body (variables are supported)</li><li>Add (global) Attachments (optional)</li><li>Click \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\"</li><li>Select \"JSON\" as \"Source\" and check \"Deliver Mode\"</li><li>Add (individual) Attachments (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Select the \"File\"</li><li>Check \"Start\", \"Stop\" and \"Pause\" (optional)</li><li>Click \"OK\"</li></ol>The Draft Message is saved as Template in your Current Account and for each Recipient a New Message is automagically saved in your Outbox (\"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\"). Ready for Delivery: \"File -&gt; Send Unsent Messages\"\n\n\n<strong>Step by Step:</strong> (Spreadsheet)\nScreenshots: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205600.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205601.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Draft Message</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205621.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mail Merge Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205623.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview File Dialog</a> | <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205624.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Message Dialog</a>\n<ol><li>Create a New Message (\"File -&gt; New -&gt; Message\")</li><li>Add the Variable(s) to To, e.g.: <em>{{Email}}</em> or <em>{{FirstName}} {{LastName}} &lt;{{Email}}&gt;</em></li><li>Add other Recipients to Cc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add other Recipients to Bcc (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Subject (variables are supported)</li><li>Add the Body (variables are supported)</li><li>Add (global) Attachments (optional)</li><li>Click \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\"</li><li>Select \"Spreadsheet\" as \"Source\" and check \"Deliver Mode\"</li><li>Add (individual) Attachments (optional) (variables are supported)</li><li>Select the \"File\" and check \"Sheet Name\"</li><li>Check \"Start\", \"Stop\" and \"Pause\" (optional)</li><li>Click \"OK\"</li></ol>The Draft Message is saved as a Template in your Current Account and for each Recipient a New Message is automagically saved in your Outbox (\"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\"). Ready for Delivery: \"File -&gt; Send Unsent Messages\"\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Tutorials:</strong> (External)\n\nChris Bryson has published two videos:\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l8aOcsojVEo\" rel=\"nofollow\">How to Mail Merge with Thunderbird</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mcwJuyt_xnM\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mail Merge Attachments with Thunderbird Email</a>\n\nRaffael Herrmann has published a guide (German):\n<a href=\"https://code-bude.net/2016/11/04/serienmails-mit-thunderbird-erstellen/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Serienmails mit Thunderbird erstellen</a>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Deliver Mode:</strong>\nMail Merge supports \"Save as Draft\", \"Send Later\" (default) and \"Send Now\"  as \"Deliver Mode\" for the individual and personalized messages.\n\n<strong>Use \"Send Now\" as \"Deliver Mode\" at your own risk!</strong>\nIt is strongly recommended to use \"Send Later\" as \"Deliver Mode\" and to check the individual and personalized messages in the folder \"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\". Bugs in Thunderbird, bugs in Mail Merge and bugs in other add-ons may lead to unexpected and undesired results.\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Attachments:</strong> (Global)\nGlobal Attachments, i.e. attachments that are the same for every recipient, can be added normally using the toolbarbutton \"Attach\".\n\n\n<strong>Attachments:</strong> (Individual)\nIndividual Attachments, i.e. attachments that are different for every recipient, can be added in the \"Attachments\" field in the Mail Merge Dialog, e.g.:\n<code>{{Attachment}}</code>\n<code>C:\\Path\\To\\File\\{{Attachment}}</code>\n\nMultiple (individual) attachments can be separated by line breaks, e.g.:\n<code>C:\\Path\\To\\File\\{{Attachment1}}\nC:\\Path\\To\\File\\{{Attachment2}}\nC:\\Path\\To\\File\\{{Attachment3}}</code>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>CSV:</strong>\n<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comma-separated_values\" rel=\"nofollow\">Comma-separated values</a>\n<code>records are separated by line breaks (\\r, \\n, \\r\\n)\nfields are separated by field delimiters (comma, semicolon, colon, tab)\nfields may be enclosed within text delimiters (double quote, single quote, none)\nfields with embedded line breaks must be enclosed within text delimiters\nfields with embedded field delimiters must be enclosed within text delimiters\nfields with embedded text delimiters must be enclosed within text delimiters\nembedded text delimiters must be doubled\nfirst record must contain column names</code>\n\n\n<strong>CSV:</strong> (Example)\n<code>FirstName,LastName,Gender,Email,Attachment\nJohn,Doe,m,john.doe@example.com,C:\\MyFile.pdf</code>\n\n\n<strong>Character Set:</strong> (Recommendation)\n<a href=\"https://encoding.spec.whatwg.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Character Sets Supported by Thunderbird</a>\n<em>windows-1252</em> (Windows)\n<em>utf-8</em> (Linux &amp; Mac)\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>JSON:</strong> (Array of Arrays)\nMail Merge supports UTF-8 encoded files in JSON format with Array of Arrays.\n\n<strong>JSON:</strong> (Array of Arrays) (Example)\n<code>[\n[\"FirstName\",\"LastName\",\"Gender\",\"Email\",\"Attachment\"],\n[\"John\",\"Doe\",\"m\",\"john.doe@example.com\",\"C:\\\\MyFile.pdf\"]\n]</code>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Spreadsheet:</strong>\nSupport for spreadsheets is based on <a href=\"https://sheetjs.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">SheetJS</a>. See: <a href=\"https://github.com/sheetjs/js-xlsx#file-formats\" rel=\"nofollow\">File Formats supported by SheetJS</a>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Batch:</strong> (Start, Stop and Pause)\n<em>Start</em>: Number of the First Message (optional)\n<em>Stop</em>: Number of the Last Message (optional)\n<em>Pause</em>: Pause between Messages in Seconds (optional) (variables are supported)\n\n\n<strong>Pause:</strong> (Advanced)\nThe \"Pause\" field supports fixed and random pauses as well as variables, e.g.:\nFixed Pause: <em>10</em> (Pause 10 seconds)\nRandom Pause: <em>10-60</em> (Pause between 10 and 60 seconds)\nVariables: <em>{{Pause}}</em>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Send Later:</strong>\nMail Merge supports <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/addon/send-later-3\" rel=\"nofollow\">Send Later</a>:\n<a href=\"http://blog.kamens.us/send-later#mailmerge\" rel=\"nofollow\">User Guide</a>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Line Breaks:</strong>\nThunderbird uses an HTML editor internally. You can create line breaks with &lt;br&gt;.\n\n\n<strong>Links and Images:</strong>\nThunderbird uses an HTML editor internally. You can create (individual) links and (individual) images with \"Insert -&gt; HTML\", e.g.:\nLink: <em>&lt;a href=\"{{link}}\"&gt;</em>\nImage: <em>&lt;img src=\"{{image}}\"&gt;</em>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Preview File Dialog:</strong>\nScreenshot: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205623.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview File Dialog</a>\nThe \"Preview File Dialog\" offers you the chance to briefly check the file, i.e. CSV, JSON or Spreadsheet. <strong>It is no adequate compensation for inspecting the files themselves!</strong>\n\n\n<strong>Preview Message Dialog:</strong>\nScreenshot: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205624.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preview Message Dialog</a>\nThe \"Preview Message Dialog\" offers you the chance to briefly check the messages. <strong>It is no adequate compensation for inspecting the individual and personalized messages themselves!</strong>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Deliver Mode Warning</strong>\nScreenshot: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205632.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Deliver Mode Warning</a>\n<strong>Use \"Send Now\" as \"Deliver Mode\" at your own risk!</strong>\nIt is strongly recommended to use \"Send Later\" as \"Deliver Mode\" and to check the individual and personalized messages in the folder \"Local Folders -&gt; Outbox\". Bugs in Thunderbird, bugs in Mail Merge and bugs in other add-ons may lead to unexpected and undesired results.\n\n\n<strong>Recipients Reminder:</strong>\nScreenshot: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205625.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Recipients Reminder</a>\nThe \"Recipients Reminder\" shall prevent accidentally clicking on \"Send Now\" or \"Send Later\". To start Mail Merge please click \"Cancel\" and use the menu \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\" or the toolbarbutton \"Mail Merge\". The \"Recipients Reminder\" can be activated and deactivated in the Mail Merge Options (\"Tools -&gt; Add-ons Preferences -&gt; Mail Merge\"). Threshold: <em>extensions.mailmerge.recipients</em>\n\n\n<strong>Variables Reminder:</strong>\nScreenshot: <a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/user-media/previews/full/205/205626.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">Variables Reminder</a>\nThe \"Variables Reminder\" shall prevent accidentally clicking on \"Send Now\" or \"Send Later\". To start Mail Merge please click \"Cancel\" and use the menu \"File -&gt; Mail Merge\" or the toolbarbutton \"Mail Merge\". The \"Variables Reminder\" can be activated and deactivated in the Mail Merge Options (\"Tools -&gt; Add-ons Preferences -&gt; Mail Merge\").\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name}}</em>\nThe variable will be replaced by the value of the field <em>name</em>, e.g.:\n<em>{{FirstName}}</em>: the variable will be replaced by the value of the field <em>FirstName</em>\n<em>{{LastName}}</em>: the variable will be replaced by the value of the field <em>LastName</em>\n<em>{{PrimaryEmail}}</em>: the variable will be replaced by the value of the field <em>PrimaryEmail</em>\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|if|then}}</em>\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> equals <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|if|then|else}}</em>\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> equals <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|*|if|then|else}}</em> (includes)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> <em>includes</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|^|if|then|else}}</em> (starts with)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> <em>starts with</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|$|if|then|else}}</em> (ends with)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> <em>ends with</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|==|if|then|else}}</em> (equal to) (number)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> is <em>equal to</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|&gt;|if|then|else}}</em> (greater than) (number)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> is <em>greater than</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|&gt;=|if|then|else}}</em> (greater than or equal to) (number)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> is <em>greater than or equal to</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|&lt;|if|then|else}}</em> (less than) (number)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> is <em>less than</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n<strong>Variable:</strong> <em>{{name|&lt;=|if|then|else}}</em> (less than or equal to) (number)\nIf the value of the field <em>name</em> is <em>less than or equal to</em> <em>if</em>, then the variable will be replaced by <em>then</em>, else by <em>else</em>.\n\n\n<strong>Nested Variables:</strong>\nVariables can be nested. For example: To create individual emails only for your premium customers, you can add something like this in the To field:\n{{Premium|x|{{Email}}}}\n\n\n<strong>Warning:</strong> (Variables in the From / To / Cc / Bcc / Reply fields)\nAdvanced variables like \"includes\", \"starts with\" and \"ends with\" as well as the \"numbers\" may not work as expected in the From / To / Cc / Bcc / Reply fields!\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Address Book:</strong>\n<a href=\"https://dxr.mozilla.org/comm-central/source/comm/mailnews/addrbook/public/nsIAbCard.idl\" rel=\"nofollow\">Addressbook Properties Supported by Thunderbird</a>\n<code><em>{{FirstName}}</em>\n<em>{{LastName}}</em>\n<em>{{DisplayName}}</em>\n<em>{{NickName}}</em>\n<em>{{PrimaryEmail}}</em>\n<em>{{SpouseName}}</em>\n<em>{{FamilyName}}</em>\n<em>{{SecondEmail}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeAddress}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeAddress2}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeCity}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeState}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeZipCode}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeCountry}}</em>\n<em>{{WebPage2}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkAddress}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkAddress2}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkCity}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkState}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkZipCode}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkCountry}}</em>\n<em>{{WebPage1}}</em>\n<em>{{HomePhone}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkPhone}}</em>\n<em>{{FaxNumber}}</em>\n<em>{{PagerNumber}}</em>\n<em>{{CellularNumber}}</em>\n<em>{{JobTitle}}</em>\n<em>{{Department}}</em>\n<em>{{Company}}</em>\n<em>{{Custom1}}</em>\n<em>{{Custom2}}</em>\n<em>{{Custom3}}</em>\n<em>{{Custom4}}</em>\n<em>{{Notes}}</em>\n<em>{{AnniversaryYear}}</em>\n<em>{{AnniversaryMonth}}</em>\n<em>{{AnniversaryDay}}</em>\n<em>{{BirthYear}}</em>\n<em>{{BirthMonth}}</em>\n<em>{{BirthDay}}</em>\n<em>{{_AimScreenName}}</em>\n<em>{{_GoogleTalk}}</em>\n<em>{{_Yahoo}}</em>\n<em>{{_Skype}}</em>\n<em>{{_QQ}}</em>\n<em>{{_MSN}}</em>\n<em>{{_ICQ}}</em>\n<em>{{_JabberId}}</em>\n<em>{{_IRC}}</em></code>\n\n\n<strong>Address Book:</strong>\n<a href=\"https://freeshell.de/~kaosmos/morecols-en.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">MoreFunctionsForAddressBook</a>\n<code><em>{{MFFABcustom1}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom2}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom3}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom4}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom5}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom6}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom7}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom8}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom9}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABcustom10}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABemail1}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABemail2}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABemail3}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABemail4}}</em>\n<em>{{MFFABemail5}}</em></code>\n\n\n<strong>Address Book:</strong>\n<a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/addon/gcontactsync/\" rel=\"nofollow\">gContactSync</a>\n<code><em>{{ThirdEmail}}</em>\n<em>{{FourthEmail}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeFaxNumber}}</em>\n<em>{{OtherNumber}}</em>\n<em>{{PrimaryEmailType}}</em>\n<em>{{SecondEmailType}}</em>\n<em>{{ThirdEmailType}}</em>\n<em>{{FourthEmailType}}</em>\n<em>{{WorkPhoneType}}</em>\n<em>{{HomePhoneType}}</em>\n<em>{{FaxNumberType}}</em>\n<em>{{CellularNumberType}}</em>\n<em>{{PagerNumberType}}</em>\n<em>{{HomeFaxNumberType}}</em>\n<em>{{OtherNumberType}}</em>\n<em>{{WebPage1Type}}</em>\n<em>{{WebPage2Type}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation0}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation1}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation2}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation3}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation4}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation5}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation0Type}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation1Type}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation2Type}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation3Type}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation4Type}}</em>\n<em>{{Relation5Type}}</em></code>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>CardBook:</strong>\n<a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/addon/cardbook/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CardBook</a>\n<code><em>{{dirPrefId}}</em>\n<em>{{cardurl}}</em>\n<em>{{etag}}</em>\n<em>{{updated}}</em>\n<em>{{deleted}}</em>\n<em>{{created}}</em>\n<em>{{lastname}}</em>\n<em>{{firstname}}</em>\n<em>{{othername}}</em>\n<em>{{prefixname}}</em>\n<em>{{suffixname}}</em>\n<em>{{fn}}</em>\n<em>{{nickname}}</em>\n<em>{{bday}}</em>\n<em>{{gender}}</em>\n<em>{{adr}}</em>\n<em>{{tel}}</em>\n<em>{{email}}</em>\n<em>{{mailer}}</em>\n<em>{{tz}}</em>\n<em>{{geo}}</em>\n<em>{{title}}</em>\n<em>{{role}}</em>\n<em>{{agent}}</em>\n<em>{{org}}</em>\n<em>{{categories}}</em>\n<em>{{note}}</em>\n<em>{{prodid}}</em>\n<em>{{sortstring}}</em>\n<em>{{uid}}</em>\n<em>{{rev}}</em>\n<em>{{url}}</em>\n<em>{{version}}</em>\n<em>{{class1}}</em>\n<em>{{key}}</em>\n<em>{{impp}}</em>\n<em>{{others}}</em>\n<em>{{photo}}</em>\n<em>{{value}}</em>\n<em>{{localURI}}</em>\n<em>{{URI}}</em>\n<em>{{extension}}</em>\n<em>{{logo}}</em>\n<em>{{value}}</em>\n<em>{{localURI}}</em>\n<em>{{URI}}</em>\n<em>{{extension}}</em>\n<em>{{sound}}</em>\n<em>{{value}}</em>\n<em>{{localURI}}</em>\n<em>{{URI}}</em>\n<em>{{extension}}</em>\n<em>{{kind}}</em>\n<em>{{member}}</em>\n<em>{{dispn}}</em>\n<em>{{dispadr}}</em>\n<em>{{disphomeadr}}</em>\n<em>{{dispworkadr}}</em>\n<em>{{disptel}}</em>\n<em>{{disphometel}}</em>\n<em>{{dispworktel}}</em>\n<em>{{dispcelltel}}</em>\n<em>{{dispemail}}</em>\n<em>{{disphomeemail}}</em>\n<em>{{dispworkemail}}</em>\n<em>{{dispimpp}}</em>\n<em>{{dispurl}}</em>\n<em>{{pgname}}</em>\n<em>{{pg}}</em></code>\n\n\n<strong>CardBook:</strong> (Address)\n<a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/addon/cardbook/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CardBook</a>\n<code><em> {{adr}}</em>\n<em>{{adrpostoffice}}</em>\n<em>{{adrextended}}</em>\n<em>{{adrstreet}}</em>\n<em>{{adrlocality}}</em>\n<em>{{adrregion}}</em>\n<em>{{adrpostalcode}}</em>\n<em>{{adrcountry}}</em></code>\n\n\n<strong>CardBook:</strong> (Types)\n<a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/addon/cardbook/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CardBook</a>\nThe configured \"Types\" in the \"CardBook Preferences\" can be used by its \"Code\" as a first parameter for the properties address, email, impp, phone and url. For example:\n<code><em>{{adr#home}}</em>\n<em>{{adr#work}}</em>\n<em>{{email#home}}</em>\n<em>{{email#work}}</em>\n<em>{{impp#home}}</em>\n<em>{{impp#work}}</em>\n<em>{{tel#cell}}</em>\n<em>{{tel#fax}}</em>\n<em>{{tel#home}}</em>\n<em>{{tel#work}}</em>\n<em>{{url#home}}</em>\n<em>{{url#work}}</em></code>\n\nIn case you have multiple entries, you can use a number as a second parameter for the properties address, email, impp, phone and url. For example:\n<code><em>{{url#home#0}}</em>\n<em>{{url#home#1}}</em>\n<em>{{url#home#2}}</em></code>\n\n\n<strong>CardBook:</strong> (Custom Fields)\n<a href=\"https://addons.thunderbird.net/addon/cardbook/\" rel=\"nofollow\">CardBook</a>\nThe configured \"Custom Fields\" in the \"CardBook Preferences\" can be used by its \"Field Name\". For example:\n<code><em>{{others#X-CUSTOM1}}</em>\n<em>{{others#X-CUSTOM2}}</em>\n<em>{{others#X-CUSTOM3}}</em>\n<em>{{others#X-CUSTOM4}}</em></code>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Custom Headers:</strong>\nMail Merge supports <a href=\"http://kb.mozillazine.org/Custom_headers\" rel=\"nofollow\">Custom Headers</a>: \n<em>mail.compose.other.header</em>\n\n\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n<strong>Debug:</strong>\nView Log Messages in the Mailredirect extension for Mozilla Thunderbird and Mozilla SeaMonkey adds the ability to redirect one or more email messages to one or more recipients.\nThe feature of email redirecting is also known as remailing or resending.\nThe extension is an answer for <a href=\"https://bugzil.la/12916\" title=\"Bug 12916 - Allow bounce/redirect of mail messages\" rel=\"nofollow\">bug 12916</a>\n\nNot all email providers support redirection of messages. Most notably Microsoft does not support it at the moment, probably as a measure against SPAM. I think they do this in error, and also reported this to Microsoft, but unfortunately they haven't changed their policy yet.\n\nIf you run into issues with an email provider not supporting redirection of messages, please contact them and see if you can make them change their policy. You can point them to this add-on, <a href=\"https://bugzil.la/12916\" title=\"Bug 12916 - Allow bounce/redirect of mail messages\" rel=\"nofollow\">bug 12916</a>, or <a href=\"https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2822.txt\" rel=\"nofollow\">RFC2822</a> section 3.6.6.\n\nAs a workaround you can also redirect your messages through another email provider, e.g. Gmail, but this isn't always desirable, because then that email provider gains access to the messages you redirect, and those messages might contain sensitive information.","nl":"De Mailredirect-extensie voor Mozilla extension for Thunderbird has the aim to improve the printing layout of the mails, with the following features:\n\n- it gives the possibility to have the date of the message in a format similar to the one used in messages panel;\n- it can also modify deeply the view of the attachments' list, inserting it in the headers, just after the recipients;\n- it can add a border arorund the headers;\n- it can hide the headers;\n- it can truncate the headers' lines too long;\n- it can hide the images in the message;\n- it can hide the inline attachments in printing, even if you view them by default;\n- it can add the user name before the headers;\n- it can delete the card header in addressbook (\"Card for\");\n- it can print contacts with just name and email address;\n- it can print addressbook with small fonts. The default value is 10 pixel, but you can change it as you wish;\n- it can use a compact format to print from addressbook (with this option and the others you can save up to 40% of paper);\n- it can print just selected part of a message;\n- it can apply a style (color and size) to the quoted text;\n- it can give more options in printing addressbook;\n- it can use a font family and a font size in printing messages (for the whole message or just for headers);\n- it can hide always extended headers; - it can modify headers order;\n- it can set a maximum length for the text lines (default value = 90 characters). This is useful to prevent that very long text lines without newline characters can break the print layout. \n\nMoreover it gives you a fast access to two native functions of Thunderbird, pringing without progress bar and without the printer dialog.\nIt deletes also automatically in printing the .doc and .rtf attachments wrongly displayed inline, because of a wrong content-type in the message.\n\nYou can modify the settings for messages in main window from File --&gt; Printing options and the settings for addressbook from addressbook window in File --&gt; Printing options.\n\nHow print just selection in a message: go in File --&gt; Printing options in main window and enable this option. It make all templates sorted, most recently used going on top.\n\nBut You can change default behavior: simply go to <strong>Tools</strong> / <strong>Stationery options</strong>, tab <strong>Options</strong>, and un-check <strong>Enable automatic templates management</strong> checkbox. Posta Elettronica Certificata (PEC) nasce per sostituire il servizio di posta raccomandata nella comunicazione tra i professionisti, i cittadini e le istituzioni rendendo più efficiente il meccanismo di comunicazione. Il sistema, basandosi sullo standard S/MIME, certifica lo scambio di documenti tra il mittente e il destinatario della comunicazione e informa automaticamente il mittente sullo stato della comunicazione fornendo ricevute che hanno valenza legale.\n\nThunderPEC si propone come strumento per la gestione semplificata della posta elettronica certificata in Thunderbird e può essere abilitato selettivamente sui soli account PEC.\n\nUn messaggio di posta elettronica certificata è costituito da una Busta di Trasporto che contiene il messaggio di posta elettronica originale inviato dal mittente ed un allegato XML che riassume i dati della transazione. La busta di trasporto è firmata digitalmente dal gestore PEC sorgente. \n\nThunderPEC visualizza direttamente il messaggio di posta elettronica originale e offre gli strumenti per poter operare sul messaggio originale. Inoltre, gestisce le notifiche PEC inviate dai gestori PEC coinvolti nella transazione. \n\nThunderPEC semplifica la gestione delle <b>notifiche PEC</b> e delle <b>ricevute <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/a3c6fc477c3d56c1ce635eb5e5c9cea47e41f6749e6fc96bf12e54828b4d5dc3/https%3A//it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Processo_civile_telematico_%2528diritto_italiano%2529\">PCT</a> e FatturaPA</b>, attraverso la funzionalità <b>Stato del messaggio</b> che permette di avere una visione di insieme/riassuntiva delle notifiche associate ad un messaggio inviato.\n\nThunderPEC introduce <b>tre filtri rapidi (Messaggi, Notifiche, 53/94)</b> che permettono la selezione rapida dei soli messaggi PEC, delle sole notifiche PEC o dei messaggi PEC conenenti notifiche secondo la Legge 53/94.\n\nThunderPEC  implementa, inoltre, le seguenti funzionalità:\n<ul><li><b>Archiviazione delle notifiche PEC e ricevute PCT/FatturaPA</b> che offre la possibilità di salvare le notifiche PEC associate ad un messaggio, le ricevute PCT/FatturaPA ed il messaggio stesso all'interno di un file zip per l'archiviazione.</li><li><b>Cerca PA</b> per ricercare l'indirizzo PEC di un ufficio pubblico sull'infrastruttura Open Data di DigitPA (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/9d934bb98932984ad82f8b8826247a60b2de29421d8a6297c988ad8f1b63e1a6/http%3A//spcdata.digitpa.gov.it\">spcdata.digitpa.gov.it</a>).</li><li><b>Trasferisci Account</b> per trasferire i dati di un account PEC da <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/ea007840c341b208b928e4cf637e3f81a4cf22ab9f398d24e6f638cd10e8c30a/http%3A//youtu.be/uuN8pQqERek\">ThunderPEC a PocketPEC</a>.</li></ul>\nThunderPEC introduce, all'interno del menu principale, il menu ThunderPEC, composto da:\n1) <b>Account</b>: per la gestione degli account PEC.\n1.a) <b>Aggiungi</b>: per aggiungere un nuovo account PEC. Semplifica la creazione di un nuovo account per i gestori preconfigurati (Aruba PEC, Legalmail, Postecert, Vodafone PEC, Telecom Italia PEC, PostaCertificat@, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/afcc9568ec003fd863fbbd3c1b6158799dba50374d2534584496d6acf6e8fba9/http%3A//pec.istruzione.it\">pec.istruzione.it</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/0fc0aefbf2df361fdd461c2fdba4bf5ba2722e92c7d8befef18f462c9dc74a97/http%3A//pec.notariato.it\">pec.notariato.it</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/d24ab283c097c02ae95a181a4ee0c25bc1022853cb0b06f106ce12a2541b5f01/http%3A//postacertificata.notariato.it\">postacertificata.notariato.it</a>). \n1.b) <b>Seleziona</b>: per abilitare/disabilitare ThunderPEC sugli account già esistenti.\n2) <b>Tipo di ricevuta</b>: per selezionare il tipo di ricevuta di consegna desiderata.\n3) <b>P7M</b>: per attivare/disattivare la funzionalità per la correzione del bug sugli allegati p7m di Thunderbird.\n4) <b>PocketPEC</b>: per trasferire un account PEC da ThunderPEC a PocketPEC in modalità keyless.\n5) <b>Condividi/Seguici</b>: per l'interazione attraverso i social network (ad esempio, Facebook, Twitter).\n6) <b>Aiuto</b>: per visualizzare la guida.\n7) <b>Invia email al supporto</b>: per inviare un email al supporto di ThunderPEC.\n8) <b>Informazioni su ThunderPEC</b>: per visualizzare la versione dell'estensione e ulteriori informazioni aggiuntive.\n\nInoltre, per poter operare direttamente sul messaggio originale contenuto all'interno di un messaggio PEC e gestire i dati di certificazione e le ricevute, ThunderPEC aggiunge i seguenti elementi:\n\na) Il sottomenu ThunderPEC al menu Messaggio di Thunderbird\nb) Il sottomenu ThunderPEC all'interno del menu contestuale\nc) La toolbar di gestione all'interno della finestra del messaggio\nd) Il menu Thunderpec all'interno della finestra di réactions ! Cliquez sur le lien ci-dessus :-)</b>\n\nThunderbird Conversations est une extension pour Thunderbird qui comme son nom l'indique affiche vos courriers en mode conversation. Les fonctions les plus sympas sont les suivantes :\n- la vue en conversation classique qui récupère les messages de tous les dossiers, à la manière de Gmail ;\n- l'intégration de <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/243985/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Thunderbird Contacts</a> : les participants sont repérables par une infobulle, qui comprend leur avatar et profil de Facebook, Twitter…\n- la réponse rapide, avec l'autocomplétion qui vous permet de dire votre mot dans une discussion en un clin d'œil\n- les citations masquées qui améliorent la lisibilité\n- les raccourcis-clavier,\n- et quelques astuces supplémentaires à découvrir.","en-US":"<a href=\"https://github.com/protz/thunderbird-conversations/wiki\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>Website</b> (including documentation)</a> - <a href=\"https://github.com/protz/thunderbird-conversations/wiki/FAQ\" rel=\"nofollow\">FAQ</a> - <a href=\"https://github.com/protz/thunderbird-conversations/issues\" rel=\"nofollow\">Report bugs</a> - <a href=\"https://github.com/protz/thunderbird-conversations/commits/master\" rel=\"nofollow\">Track changes</a>\n\nThunderbird Conversations is a Thunderbird extension which, as the name implies, enables a conversation view in your Thunderbird. Notable features include:\n<ul><li>a regular conversation view that fetches messages from all folders, and behaves just like Gmail’s</li><li>a quick reply feature, with autocomplete, that allows you to reply to a thread in a snap,</li><li>quoted parts are collapsed,</li><li>keyboard shortcuts,</li><li>and a few other bonus features.</li></ul>\n<b>Don't forget to hit View &gt; Sort By &gt; Threaded</b> in the menus. To remove the unified folder view, hit <b>View &gt; Folders &gt; All</b>.\n\n\n<b>We welcome feedback, but only if you've read the <b><a href=\"https://github.com/protz/thunderbird-conversations/wiki/faq\" rel=\"nofollow\">FAQ</a></b> before :-)</b>\n\n<b>Known Issues with Thunderbird 68</b>\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://github.com/protz/thunderbird-conversations/issues/1361\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quick Reply is not working in 68</a>. This is a work in progress due to the changes in TB 68.</li></ul>","it":"<a href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/topic/mozilla-labs/CZbSaSpnBxE/discussion\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lascia un feedback</a> - <a href=\"http://wiki.github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>Visita il sito web</b> (documentazione inclusa)</a> - <a href=\"http://wiki.github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/faq\" rel=\"nofollow\">Consulta le FAQ</a> - <a href=\"http://github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/issues\" rel=\"nofollow\">Segnala un bug</a> - <a href=\"http://github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/commits/master\" rel=\"nofollow\">Segui le modifiche</a> - <a href=\"http://jonathan.xulforum.org/files/gcv-nightlies/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Preleva l'ultima versione di sviluppo</a>\n\n<b>I feedback sono apprezzati! Utilizzare il relativo link qui sopra per inviarne uno</b>\n\nThunderbird Conversations è un'estensione per Thunderbird che, come implica il nome stesso, permette di visualizzare le e-mail sotto forma di conversazioni. Le caratterestiche di nota sono le seguenti:\n- regolare visualizzazione sotto forma di conversazioni in modo analogo al sito web di Gmail, prendendo i messaggi da tutte le cartelle\n- integrazione con l'estensione <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/addon/243985/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Thunderbird Contacts</a>: i partecipanti hanno i tooltip nella conversazione, ed è possibile visualizzarne avatar e profili da Facebook, Twitter, etc…\n- possibilità di risposta rapida con autocompletamento\n- parti citate contratte (quindi non visibili)\n- scorciatoie da tastiera\n- alcuni altri bonus","pt-BR":"<a href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/topic/mozilla-labs/CZbSaSpnBxE/discussion\" rel=\"nofollow\">Enviar comentário</a> - <a href=\"http://wiki.github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>Site</b> (com documentação)</a> - <a href=\"http://wiki.github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/faq\" rel=\"nofollow\">Perguntas frequentes</a> - <a href=\"http://github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/issues\" rel=\"nofollow\">Comunicar erro</a> - <a href=\"http://github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/commits/master\" rel=\"nofollow\">Verificar alterações</a> - <a href=\"http://jonathan.xulforum.org/files/gcv-nightlies/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Versões mais recentes em desenvolvimento</a>\n\n<b>Comentários são bem-vindos! Veja o link para enviar comentários acima. :-)</b>\n\nO Thunderbird Conversations é uma extensão para o Thunderbird que, como o nome indica, permite um modo de conversa no seu Thunderbird.\nEntre os recursos dignos de nota, temos:\n- um modo de conversa que busca mensagens em todas as pastas, funcionando igual ao do Gmail;\n- integração com a extensão <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/pt-BR/thunderbird/addon/mozilla-labs-contacts/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mozilla Labs: Contacts</a>: ao passar o mouse sobre os participantes de uma conversa, são exibidas informações sobre eles, podendo ser exibidos com avatar e perfil do Facebook, Twitter, etc;\n- um recurso que permite responder diretamente nas mensagens de uma conversa, num piscar de olhos e com preenchimento automático;\n- texto de mensagens anteriores são ocultadas;\n- atalhos de teclado;\n- e alguns outros recursos extras.","sv-SE":"<a href=\"https://groups.google.com/d/topic/mozilla-labs/CZbSaSpnBxE/discussion\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ge oss feedback</a> - <a href=\"http://wiki.github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View\" rel=\"nofollow\"><b>Webbplats</b> (inkluderar dokumentation)</a> - <a href=\"http://wiki.github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/faq\" rel=\"nofollow\">Vanliga frågor och svar</a> - <a href=\"http://github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/issues\" rel=\"nofollow\">Rapportera buggar</a> - <a href=\"http://github.com/protz/GMail-Conversation-View/commits/master\" rel=\"nofollow\">Spåra ändringar</a> - <a href=\"http://jonathan.xulforum.org/files/gcv-nightlies/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Senaste utvecklingsversionerna</a>\n\n<b>Vi älskar att få feedback! mail folders in Thunderbird. \n\nThis extension adds an extra toolbar to Thunderbird. When you drag a mail folder to it, you get a fully customizable shortcut to that mail folder. This supports full drag and drop, like the corresponding folder in the folder tree - You can drag messages on it to move/copy them to the folder, and access the bookmarked folders through keyboard shortcuts.\n\nThis is handy when you have a large tree of folders for clients or projects, but use only a few of them at the same time.\n\nThe Category feature adds more usability by adding distinct areas to work in; this can make it easier to focus on a task that needs just a subset of the folders visible. There is also excellent integration with the Thunderbird tabbed interface provided since Tb version 3.","de":"Bookmark Mail Ordner in Thunderbird. \n\nDiese Erweiterung erzeugt eine neue Werkzeugleiste in Thunderbird. Sie können damit auch Mails per drag &amp; drop verschieben / kopieren. \n\nDies ist praktisch wenn man eine große Verzeichnisstruktur mit vielen Ordnern hat (z.B. für Kunden, Projekte) aber normalerweise nur mit einer kleineren Auswahl davon arbeitet. \n\nDurch die neuen Kategorien lässt sich die Arbeit mit Mails noch einfacher strukturieren. Damit lassen sich die wichtigsten Ordner einer Kategorie (z.B. Arbeit / Hobby etc.) darstellen - spezielle Ordner wie z.B. Posteingang können permanent angezeigt werden.
